<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHARING BLAME OF 'MORAL MUTANTS' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gary Abrams' "Moral Mutants" article on Michael Josephson's ethics research was 
shocking and sad. 
</P>
<P>
Young American adults have learned selfishness from their parents, public 
officials and business leaders. It's a sad commentary on the quality of 
American life and the prospects for the future. My hope is that the shocking 
truth of low and declining morals and ethical standards will be a catalyst for 
change, but I'm not optimistic. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN LICHTER 
</P>
<P>
Santa Monica 
</P>
</TEXT>
