<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: ART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Art on the Tube: New York painter Marilyn Minter has taken to the airwaves to 
advertise her artworks with MTV-style commercials seen on late-night shows like 
"Late Night With David Letterman" and "Nightline" and "The Arsenio Hall Show." 
</P>
<P>
The ads, seen in the New York area only, are hawking her "100 Food Porn" 
exhibit at a Manhattan gallery which opened Thursday. The paintings sell for 
$3,500 each. And the cost of producing and airing six television ads is 
$16,500. Minter says the price tag is less than a splashy ad in an art 
magazine. CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
</TEXT>
