<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Empress Brooke?: Brooke Shields stirred up the Japanese media recently when she 
dropped in on an old friend, Crown Prince Naruhito. Shields was in the country 
last week to mark the 100th anniversary of the Harry Winston jewelry store and 
the future emperor invited her to stop by the Imperial Palace. 
</P>
<P>
The two first met five years ago at Princeton University while Shields was an 
undergraduate and Naruhito visited the campus on his way back from his alma 
mater Oxford University. The bachelor prince was the object of press attention 
earlier this year when his younger brother, Prince Aya, got married before him 
and Shields' visit stirred up the reporters again. One newspaper resurrected a 
photo of Naruhito's college dorm room with a poster of Shields prominent on the 
wall. CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Shields 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
