<HEADLINE>
<P>
EDISON GETS BIG QUARTER, BIG VICTORY; 
</P>
<P>
SUNSET LEAGUE: CHARGERS SCORE 20 IN SECOND QUARTER AND BEAT OCEAN VIEW, 23-17, 
TO WIN LEAGUE TITLE WITH UNDEFEATED RECORD. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FERNANDO DOMINGUEZ, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HUNTINGTON BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Though they mounted most of their serious drives only in the second quarter, 
Edison High School held on to defeat Ocean View, 23-17, Thursday night in front 
of 3,400 at Huntington Beach High. 
</P>
<P>
Edison (8-1, 6-0 in the Sunset League), got three touchdown passes by senior 
quarterback Josh Gingrich and scored 20 points in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Ocean View dropped to 4-2-1, 2-2-1. The Seahawks' hopes for a playoff berth 
rest, in part, on the outcome of their game against Huntington Beach next 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
"We've got to beat Huntington," Ocean View Coach Howard Isom said. Edison has 
completed its league season. 
</P>
<P>
Edison got another strong performance from Gingrich, who completed 18 of 25 
passes for 268 yards. He entered the game with 1,643 yards passing and 12 
touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
The 6-foot, 190-pound quarterback got Edison's offense rolling during the 
Chargers' second possession of the second quarter, when he connected with wide 
receiver Mike Cunningham on a 51-yard pass play with 7 minutes 3 seconds 
remaining in the half. 
</P>
<P>
Six minutes later, Gingrich, rolling out to his right and under heavy pursuit 
by at least two Ocean View defenders, teamed with Cunningham on a 10-yard pass 
play for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
Gingrich and the Chargers then gained possession at their 20-yard line with 
1:04 left before the half and drove 80 yards for another score. 
</P>
<P>
The key plays in the drive were a 40-yard reception by wide receiver Ryan 
Blanchard, who tipped the ball away from two defenders to make the catch, and a 
24-yard run by junior tailback Travis Balding that moved the ball to the Ocean 
View 16. From there, Gingrich hit junior tight end Rod Lippincott on a crossing 
pattern for a 20-3 halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
Ocean View, which had opened the scoring on a 42-yard field goal by Ron 
Lightner on its first possession of the game, cut the Edison lead to 20-10 in 
the third quarter on a 75-yard run by quarterback Randy Karliner. 
</P>
<P>
After Lightner's field goal in the fourth quarter, Ocean View scored its final 
points on a four-yard run by fullback Matt Barry with 49 seconds left. 
</P>
</TEXT>
