<HEADLINE>
<P>
LANDRY SCORES TWO TOUCHDOWNS TO LEAD SAVANNA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB BORSUM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Leon Landry scored two touchdowns in Savanna High School's 21-10 victory over 
Western Thursday at Western High. 
</P>
<P>
Landry scored on a 70-yard run on the game's second play from scrimmage. 
</P>
<P>
He also scored from the one-yard line with six seconds left in the third 
quarter to ensure the victory for Savanna (5-2-2, 2-1-1 in league). Landry also 
gained 117 of Savanna's 275 rushing yards. 
</P>
<P>
The loss virtually eliminates Western (4-3-2, 1-2-1) from post-season play. 
</P>
<P>
Savanna dominated the first half and took a 14-0 lead on Brook Bell's two-yard 
run with 5 minutes 31 seconds left in the first quarter. The Rebels held 
Western to 32 yards rushing in nine carries and 71 yards passing in the first 
half. Gilbert Brito was intercepted three times in the first half, twice by 
Hien Nguyen. 
</P>
<P>
Brito scored Western's only touchdown on a nine-yard run in the final 1:46 of 
the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
At the start of the third quarter, Western returned the kick to the Savanna 46, 
then Brito ran the ball to the Savanna 12 on first down. Shane Foss fumbled the 
ball at the three on the next play and Savanna's Marty Garcia recovered the 
ball at the 10 to stop the drive. BOB BORSUM 
</P>
</TEXT>
