<TEXT>
<P>
In other league finals: 
</P>
<P>
Century League -- Santa Ana Valley hadn't won a boys' cross-country league 
championship since 1969, but the Falcons placed four runners in the top 10 at 
Yorba Regional Park to edge El Modena for the title. 
</P>
<P>
Canyon, with freshmen Kim Nelson and Laura Flatauer placing first and third, 
won the girls' varsity league championship with 36 points to 54 for Foothill. 
</P>
<P>
Villa Park senior Danny Simon easily topped the boys' field, covering the 
course in 15:03 to beat Santa Ana Valley's Peter Reyes (15:12) and El Modena's 
Austin Brent (15:13). 
</P>
<P>
Reyes, a sophomore, was joined by teammates Juan Arvizu (fifth, 15:24), Jerry 
Gomez (seventh, 15:32) and Lucio Brito (eighth, 15:35) in the top 10. 
</P>
<P>
"The kids were really up for this one," Falcon Coach George Payan said. "We got 
a lot of support from the community, staff and students to back us up." 
</P>
<P>
Canyon's girls' team was aided by a fifth-place finish by senior Cathy Lee in 
18:32. El Modena sophomore Kristina Dahlberg finished second to Nelson in 
18:14, and sophomore Allison Myers of Foothill finished fourth in 18:17. TOM 
BIRSCHBACH 
</P>
