<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: TRICK-OR-TREATERS SHOT WITH BBS; 2 ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two teen-agers received minor injuries and two others were arrested after 
allegedly firing a BB gun at a group of youngsters trick-or-treating in Santa 
Clarita Park, sheriff's deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
A 15-year-old Saugus boy and a 17-year-old Encino youth were arrested on 
suspicion of assault and weapons possession, Sheriff's Lt. William Bengtson 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The youths, whose names were not released because they are juveniles, were 
turned over to their parents. 
</P>
<P>
Officers were patrolling in the 27000 block of Sycamore Creek Drive at 8:20 
p.m. when they were flagged down by a teen-ager who said two youths had fired 
at the group, Bengtson said. 
</P>
<P>
The officers found a gray BMW carrying the two suspects and confiscated a 
pellet rifle, a BB gun and a set of nunchakus, a martial-arts weapon. 
</P>
<P>
A 15-year-old girl suffered a welt on her hip and a 13-year-old boy was hit on 
the shoulder. 
</P>
