<HEADLINE>
<P>
RANKED AS TOP TWO, UCLA AND HAWAII TO PLAY SATURDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal State Long Beach women's volleyball team is the defending national 
champion, but UCLA and Hawaii will be playing the key match during a four-team 
tournament this weekend at UCLA's Pauley Pavilion. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA (21-1), the nation's top-ranked team, is playing host to the four-team Big 
West-Pacific 10 Conference challenge tonight and Saturday night, with matches 
beginning each night at 5 and 7. 
</P>
<P>
The challenge will culminate Saturday night with the matchup between UCLA and 
No. 2 Hawaii (19-3) in the 7 p.m. game. 
</P>
<P>
No. 13 Long Beach (18-7) took some luster off that match by upsetting Hawaii, 
15-5, 10-15, 8-15, 15-7, 15-9, Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
Tonight's matches: USC (10-9) vs. Hawaii and UCLA vs. Long Beach. The Trojans 
and 49ers will open Saturday's competition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
