<P>
FDIC Rejects Bid for Continental Stake: The Federal Deposit Insurance Corp. has 
rejected a $112-million bid by investors and management for the federal 
agency's 26% stake in Continental Bank Corp., the bank firm said. 
</P>
<P>
The FDIC acquired all of Chicago-based Continental when the bank failed in 1984 
and has slowly been selling it off. The 26% stake is its last chunk. FDIC 
spokesman Alan Whitney said the FDIC board voted 4-0 to reject the bid because 
it "was not in the best interests of the FDIC." He declined to say why. 
</P>
