<P>
PLAYS FOR KIDS: Robert Redford has selected longtime South Coast Repertory 
staffer Jerry Patch to take charge of a new national children's theater program 
based at the Sundance Institute in Utah. . . . Patch will remain at SCR as a 
literary adviser but will help the institute recruit major writers for 
children's projects. "The tradition in Europe is that the best writers also 
write for children," Patch says. "The level of that literature is very high." 
