<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Zan Dubin and George Frank 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGING TIMES: In 1980, Disneyland security gave the bum's rush to two men 
caught dancing together. 
</P>
<P>
This year on Nov. 30, the park hosts the third private party thrown by AIDS 
Project Los Angeles and the AIDS Service Foundation of Orange County. . . . 
"About 90% are going to be gay, but that's not the point," says an AIDS Project 
spokesman. "Disneyland sees it as a fund-raiser for the AIDS cause, not as 'gay 
night.' If they have any misgivings or apprehensions, they definitely don't 
show it." Zan Dubin and George Frank 
