<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: AMBURGEY LEADS IN FUND RAISING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY ANNE PEREZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Orville Amburgey, who is seeking reelection to the City Council, leads fund 
raising among five candidates seeking two seats in Tuesday's election. 
</P>
<P>
According to records filed with the city clerk's office, Amburgey has raised 
$46,527 so far, about $10,000 more than incumbent Mayor Peter F. Buffa. 
</P>
<P>
Buffa, who got a late start in campaigning this year, has raised $35,659. About 
half of that has been raised since Oct. 1. Buffa has also raised the most money 
-- more than $3,000 -- from political action committees. 
</P>
<P>
Challenger Arlene Schafer raised only $3,895 in the October reporting period, 
but has accumulated a total of $21,355 this year. Schafer, who is a former 
mayor, is seeking a third non-consecutive term on the City Council. 
</P>
<P>
Although Amburgey has raised the most money, he has spent only $8,290 in the 
same period on advertising, signs and fund-raisers. Both he and Buffa have 
hired professional consultants to help run their campaigns. 
</P>
<P>
"I will assure you that it all has a place to go," Amburgey said. 
</P>
<P>
Trailing in fund raising are challengers Jay Humphrey and Karen McGlinn. 
Humphrey has raised $5,707, while McGlinn has raised $2,908. MARY ANNE PEREZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
