<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; 
</P>
<P>
FREE BUS RIDE WILL TOUR CITY LAND BUYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEN HALL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A tour bus will leave City Hall at 8:30 a.m. Saturday for a free public tour of 
open spaces that have been targeted for purchase by the city. 
</P>
<P>
City officials will accompany the riders on the 46-passenger bus to view the 
properties, including orange groves in the northwest areas of town and the 
Kinoshita farm just off Del Obispo Street. 
</P>
<P>
The tour will also include a hilltop view of the city from the ridgelines near 
Laguna Niguel. 
</P>
<P>
City voters approved the purchase of these properties with the passage of a 
$21-million general obligation bond in April. This week, the council voted to 
buy the 56-acre Kinoshita farm for $9.5 million. 
</P>
<P>
Tour participants will be doing some short hiking and should wear comfortable 
clothes. For more information, call (714) 493-5911. LEN HALL 
</P>
</TEXT>
