<HEADLINE>
<P>
CORONA DEL MAR WATER POLO TEAM LOSES COIN FLIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ARA NAJARIAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Corona del Mar High School's water polo team, the top-ranked team in the county 
for six of the past eight weeks, will be the third-seeded team from the Sea 
View League in the Southern Section playoffs after losing a coin flip Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Newport Harbor won the toss and will be the top-seeded team, and University 
will be seeded second. Corona del Mar, University and Newport Harbor finished 
tied for the league championship with 5-1 records. ARA NAJARIAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA110290-0171 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 302003 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
November 2, 1990, Friday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
