<P>
DAMAGED JETLINER LANDS SAFELY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An American Airlines DC-10 jetliner flying from London to Dallas with 242 
people on board made a safe emergency landing today at New York's Kennedy 
International Airport after blowing a tire on takeoff and suffering damage to a 
wing flap. 
</P>
<P>
Scores of emergency vans, ambulances and police vehicles were on standby for 
the landing of American Airlines Flight 51, carrying 225 passengers and a crew 
of 17, said Port Authority spokesman Allen Morrison. 
</P>
<P>
"It landed safely, rolling under its own power," Morrison said. 
</P>
<P>
There was no visible smoke or other problems when the plane landed. 
</P>
<P>
The plane first circled the airport, then landed on Kennedy's longest runway. 
</P>
